The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Saturday, September 18, 2004 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Sept. 17: An alert was today sent to the administration in Birbhum and Murshidabad warning against flood even as rain over the past 10 days flooded low-lying areas in Nadia and North 24-Parganas.

 Rain in Jharkhand is threatening Birbhum and Murshidabad as water from reservoirs on the Brahmani and the Mayurakshi have been released. Relief minister Hafiz Alam Sairani said more than 500,000 people were affected. 

 Calcutta: The Trinamul Congress showcaused MLA Nayana Bandopadhyay on Friday for joining forces with the Congress. 

 Calcutta: Mandira Chowdhury, who identified herself as a ?person interested in education?, sought action against former Rabindra Bharati University VC Pabitra Sarkar in the high court. Sarkar had served in top academic posts minus papers certifying his Chicago University PhD. 

 Midnapore: The fast-track court in Jhargram has jailed Purna Chandra Mahato for 10 years for raping and kidnapping a minor girl.




